SIMPLE: touter
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Touter
<hw>Tout"er</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>One who seeks
customers, as for an inn, a public conveyance, shops, and the like:
hence, an obtrusive candidate for office.</def>
<mark>[Colloq.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The prey of ring droppers, . . . duffers, <qex>touters</qex>, or
any of those bloodless sharpers who are, perhaps, better known to the
police.</q> <rj><qau>Dickens.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Touze</ent>⟦br⟧
